programme.desc: On this episode of Midwest Whitetail, Owen Reigler takes us along on the four year quest for an Iowa monarch he calls "Genesis." Season after season, no matter the bucks around to hunt, Owen Reigler prides himself on year-round preparation of his farm, honing his archery skills and attention to all the details to create hunting opportunities for mature bucks. A shining example of this, the four year saga that saw the "Genesis" buck slowly call Owen's farm home represents a story of hard work, gratitude and enjoyment of the outdoors unlike anyone else. With an ending only the footage itself can tell, this is one you don't want to miss! Congratulations to Owen once again, and we are excited to continue bringing you more big buck action as we continue into the month of October. Good luck and happy hunting!

Then, battling the early October heatwave, Mike and his two sons Tate and Xander hit the River Farm with the legendary buck "Tony" at the top of the target list. Coming down to the wire, Tate makes a perfect shot leading to another great memory made in the deer woods. We thank you as always for your support and hope you enjoy the show!

programme.title: How to Hunt Early Season Cold Fronts

Mike Reed, Owen Reigler, Josh Sparks and Gavin Koterba all have different takes on how to tackle hunting the front, and we hope this gives you some inspiration for hunts of your own over the next few days.
